values.name: Easy
values.doc: Represents a default set of easy complexity attacks. Easy complexity attacks require less effort, such as translation of a prompt into some encoding, and does not require any Large Language Model to convert or orchestrate.

values.name: Moderate
values.doc: Represents a default set of moderate complexity attacks. Moderate complexity attacks require having access to resources such as another generative AI model.

values.name: Difficult
values.doc: Represents a default set of difficult complexity attacks. Difficult complexity attacks include attacks that require access to significant resources and effort to execute an attack such as knowledge of search-based algorithms in addition to a generative AI model.

values.name: AsciiArt
values.doc: Generates visual art using ASCII characters, often used for creative or obfuscation purposes.

values.name: AsciiSmuggler
values.doc: Conceals data within ASCII characters, making it harder to detect.

values.name: Atbash
values.doc: Implements the Atbash cipher, a simple substitution cipher where each letter is mapped to its reverse.

values.name: Base64
values.doc: Encodes binary data into a text format using Base64, commonly used for data transmission.

values.name: Binary
values.doc: Converts text into binary code, representing data in a series of 0s and 1s.

values.name: Caesar
values.doc: Applies the Caesar cipher, a substitution cipher that shifts characters by a fixed number of positions.

values.name: CharacterSpace
values.doc: Alters text by adding spaces between characters, often used for obfuscation.

values.name: Jailbreak
values.doc: Injects specially crafted prompts to bypass AI safeguards, known as User Injected Prompt Attacks (UPIA).

values.name: AnsiiAttack
values.doc: Utilizes ANSI escape sequences to manipulate text appearance and behavior.

values.name: CharacterSwap
values.doc: Swaps characters within text to create variations or obfuscate the original content.

values.name: SuffixAppend
values.doc: Appends an adversarial suffix to the prompt.

values.name: StringJoin
values.doc: Joins multiple strings together, often used for concatenation or obfuscation.

values.name: UnicodeConfusable
values.doc: Uses Unicode characters that look similar to standard characters, creating visual confusion.

values.name: UnicodeSubstitution
values.doc: Substitutes standard characters with Unicode equivalents, often for obfuscation.

values.name: Diacritic
values.doc: Adds diacritical marks to characters, changing their appearance and sometimes their meaning.

values.name: Flip
values.doc: Flips characters from front to back, creating a mirrored effect.

values.name: Leetspeak
values.doc: Transforms text into Leetspeak, a form of encoding that replaces letters with similar-looking numbers or symbols.

values.name: ROT13
values.doc: Applies the ROT13 cipher, a simple substitution cipher that shifts characters by 13 positions.

values.name: Morse
values.doc: Encodes text into Morse code, using dots and dashes to represent characters.

values.name: Url
values.doc: Encodes text into URL format.

values.name: Baseline
values.doc: Represents the baseline direct adversarial probing, which is used by attack strategies as the attack objective.
